olimits (R^{n}) as a subset, and \mathop {	extrm {GL}}
olimits _{n}(R)\subseteq \mathop {\mathrm {Mat}}
olimits _{n}(R) the general linear group of n	imes n matrices over R is contained in the matrix ring.

We see that the adjugate A^{*} of A can be computed for any ring (where the components of A^{*} are the minors of A, i.e., (A^{*})_{i,j} equals the determinant of A where we delete row i and column j). Hence
A^{-1}=\frac {1}{\det (A)}A^{*}
